<paragraph id="20A430F9D5EEB74F1F0C84CC75E8A1C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="229833162333549E44A49424A1DE06D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Flowering from June to October, fruiting from September to December.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="86D51F93F219EB8A0E3DD80009808C06" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B84928B8709BEFE09F49F6910E029F6C" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB0FCC952747497365E4184C3C6CB29C" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The specific epithet refers to Mount 
<taxonomicName id="61967D7A39A258E259D99F086C5EDBDF" genus="Danxia" lsidName="Danxia" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="genus">Danxia</taxonomicName>
, the locality of the type collection. The Chinese name of the new species is here given as 
<normalizedToken id="14B442605F807CEF32A56E6C66B5B615" originalValue="丹霞铁马鞭">丹霞铁马鞭</normalizedToken>
(
<normalizedToken id="56894C92F52FB1B6D79C1F8AAE85E7B7" originalValue="Dān">Dan</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="F27217F89A0000602EAE077EEF2BC990" originalValue="xiá">xia</normalizedToken>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7E72A07BE52669BCFABE4F7EA69C5BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
<normalizedToken id="872E2AED3DE9E0913A73698106664A07" originalValue="tiě">tie</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="D04621BDC4F73397DD3454271F76B282" originalValue="mǎ">mǎ</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="47ACEE48D8BB1E399AAFF5E00C02F9BF" originalValue="biān">bian</normalizedToken>
), in which 
<normalizedToken id="3A4502BED17D8114EB8C8E352F355CDB" originalValue="“丹霞”">&quot;丹霞&quot;</normalizedToken>
is the Chinese name for Mount 
<taxonomicName id="15C9C0BFEE30B1C49D4BC28A562D8F0F" genus="Danxia" lsidName="Danxia" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="genus">Danxia</taxonomicName>
, as well as 
<normalizedToken id="107B2EFE4228A49093BE80CF0329DAA6" originalValue="“铁马鞭”">&quot;铁马鞭&quot;</normalizedToken>
being the common name for 
<taxonomicName id="790B55C19875BFEEF39C0E2AC04740AA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Lespedeza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lespedeza pilosa" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="F501D8FBA61EFD4F2AB839A3254A4EE5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Lespedeza pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its allies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CCD8EE41898982052D7B06F469188F46" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7A12D6B1A0EA032CA1921E78F692D08E" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Distribution, ecology and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="637C62446A16CDC720133CEFD4DF6D2F" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName id="9AAAF8504EDBD391BB6BFF9AC0EE33FE" authorityName="Q. Fan, W. Y. Zhao &amp; K. W. Jiang" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Lespedeza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lespedeza danxiaensis" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="danxiaensis">
<emphasis id="793B5C15E2B132ADDC028C0B490E3D12" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Lespedeza danxiaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from a few populations on Mount 
<taxonomicName id="FE5F9CB0B711CE2B103FE3CC1A1719FD" genus="Danxia" lsidName="Danxia" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="genus">Danxia</taxonomicName>
in Renhua County, Guangdong Province of China. It was observed to occur in bushwood on the mountaintop of 
<taxonomicName id="BE228CE4EDB7B0A7181E2FE70815B923" genus="Danxia" lsidName="Danxia" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="genus">Danxia</taxonomicName>
landform at elevations between 270 and 310 m; plants in association included 
<taxonomicName id="2061E6E3C08D0DBA0E9CAC7D3CAB73F3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Osteomeles" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Osteomeles subrotunda" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subrotunda">
<emphasis id="02822BFF91A10B3F4E7EB8D8E6DC9E26" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Osteomeles subrotunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
K. Koch, 
<taxonomicName id="76A4E679A20AC68EB9D3AF903182BCB4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Abelia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Abelia chinensis" order="Dipsacales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="3040AF05A540B296852FDF1D29465530" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Abelia chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
R. Br., 
<taxonomicName id="6965316DD90DC43C7E26AF5C97E001A5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lythraceae" genus="Lagerstroemia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lagerstroemia indica" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="DF7405CC25E867B892C5F1767E2A24BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Lagerstroemia indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName id="8BDA6C0D6B794AA055ECB66E251E55E9" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella tamariscina" order="Selaginellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tamariscina">
<emphasis id="6D595DDAC29B0110BDFCD1C48C57DB2A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Selaginella tamariscina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(P. Beauv.) Spring etc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4DAC09AF005AACF677193E0BDCAB5B1E" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="2FED8F49161201CE8FBA9F032B4C576C" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9154526FCE65FCD2DDE5F6BB7E137C4C" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The known localities of 
<taxonomicName id="54CF9D3AF61563BDE22AFA882323E44D" authorityName="Q. Fan, W. Y. Zhao &amp; K. W. Jiang" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Lespedeza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lespedeza danxiaensis" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="danxiaensis">
<emphasis id="DA985F8815FE6D1CDC3632B99DF0970A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Lespedeza danxiaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are in Danxiashan National Nature Reserve where they are well protected. However, its population size is quite small. There are fewer than 100 individuals surviving in an area of about 200 m2 in the currently known localities. We carried out several field surveys in 2020 from May to October, but no other populations were found. Due to its limited distributional range and small population size, 
<taxonomicName id="BAECCF58E99E26B7AA4B10CE78ECF916" authorityName="Q. Fan, W. Y. Zhao &amp; K. W. Jiang" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Lespedeza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lespedeza danxiaensis" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="danxiaensis">
<emphasis id="4DD55D1E9AA167AC57139420051EB04D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Lespedeza danxiaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here recommended as 
<emphasis id="8C907E386735DA63134A5F30C196612A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Critically Endangered (CR, B2a)</emphasis>
according to IUCN Categories (
<bibRefCitation id="5814A04B4D998C439DE8A3E00779612F" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee" journalOrPublisher="Vol. 10. Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" publicationUrl="https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" refId="B4" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee, 2019. Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" title="Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee." url="https://www.iucnredlist.org/resources/redlistguidelines" year="2019">IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
